snippet: Eight million people have signed up for health insurance under the Affordable Care Act, including what the White House said were a sufficient number of young, healthy adults needed to maintain the plan’s viability.
abstract: Pres Obama announces eight million people have signed up for health insurance under Affordable Care Act, including what White House says is sufficient number of young, healthy adults; critical milestone is reached that might counter election-year attacks by Republicans on law’s success and viability; critics caution that promising top-line numbers are not by themselves proof of success.

byline.original: By MARK LANDLER and MICHAEL D. SHEAR

lead_paragraph: Eight million people have signed up for health insurance under the Affordable Care Act, including what the White House said were a sufficient number of young, healthy adults needed to maintain the plan’s viability.

headline.main: Enrollments Exceed Obama’s Target for Health Care Act
headline.print_headline: Signups Exceed Obama’s Goal for Health Act
